  The hands and the elbows wrap around the inside of the thighs and catch the ankles in preparation for <a href='./Pose/tortoise_bind'>Tortoise (Kūrmāsana)</a> pose.  The gaze is down.</p></li></ul><ul><li><h5>Benefits:</h5><p class='text'>Stretches the insides and backs of the legs.  Stimulates the abdominal organs.  Strengthens the spine.  Calms the brain.  Releases groin.  Releases the elbows.</p></li></ul></section>        </section>

